supportTasks.typeAnnotation:
Combines topic modeling and structure learning with a single-column type prediction based on the Sherlock model. Two types of context are used:
- Global, the set of all cell values in the table;
- Local, the set of independently predicted semantic types of the neighboring columns in the same table. The type annotation is achieved using column-wise features including character embeddings, word embeddings, paragraph embeddings as well as column statistics.

supportTasks.subjectDetection:
The following list of features is considered:
- Fraction of empty cells;
- Distance from the first NE-column;
- Average number of words.
Then, each column is assigned a score and the highest scoring is the S-column

supportTasks.typeAnnotation:
The likelihood of all entities of a column belonging to concept is the joint probability of all its entities belonging to the concept at the same time. Also, the type of a column is the one that most likely explains all of its components. The type is determined by: 
- Using multiple data sources; 
 - Smoothing 
 - Analysing concept co-occurrence in the table; 
 - Tuple validation and belief sharing wrt other data sources.
